  "prompt": "How can we define UPSC?",
  "response": "UPSC stands for Union Public Service Commission. It is a central agency in India authorized to conduct various examinations for recruitment to higher civil services and other government positions. These exams include the Civil Services Examination (CSE) for positions such as the Indian Administrative Service (IAS), Indian Police Service (IPS), Indian Foreign Service (IFS), and other central services and posts. The UPSC is responsible for ensuring the fair and impartial selection of competent candidates for these roles, maintaining standards and integrity in the recruitment process.",
